Neonatal aortic thrombosis as a result of congenital homocystinuria. Arterial thrombosis, that too in aorta is rare in neonates.A 4-day-old presented with non-recordable BP in lower limbs. Doppler ultrasonography of abdomen revealed aortic thrombus.Serum homocysteine level was elevated (25.5 umol/L).Thrombus resolved with subcutaneous LMW heparin therapy for 2 weeks.Congenital classic homocystinuria can rarely cause aortic thrombosis in neonatal period.